---
title: Smoky Beef Chili Includes recyclable aluminum tray
description: This classic beef chili comes together with black beans, crushed tomatoes, smoked paprika, and our spicy Tex-Mex seasoning base right in our convenient recyclable oven-ready tray for a super easy-to-assemble meal. Serve with cheddar and a dollop of sour cream, then toss the tray when you're done—all of the chili flavor, none of the chili dishes!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/67f3b47da741f53bf5cb7b92-461b4e2a.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/67f3b47da741f53bf5cb7b92-en-US.pdf
author: HelloFresh
cuisine: North America
time required: 45 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 820 kcal
  fat: 45 g
  saturated fat: 18 g
  carbohydrates: 51 g
  sugar: 17 g
  protein: 44 g
  fiber: 10 g
  sodium: 1550 mg
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/smoky-beef-chili-67f3b47da741f53bf5cb7b92
course: main course
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees.

Drain and rinse @black beans{1%can}.

Add @ground beef{10%ounce} to #oven-ready tray{1} and gently break up into small pieces using a #fork{}; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.
(For 4 servings, evenly divide beef between two trays.)

Stir in beans, @crushed tomatoes{1%can}, @beef stock concentrate{1}, @tomato paste{1%unit}, @Tex-Mex paste{1}, @smoked paprika{1%teaspoon}, and @sugar{1/4%tsp}.
(For 4, evenly divide ingredients between two trays, using 1⁄4 tsp sugar per tray.)

Bake, uncovered, on top rack (be sure your oven has preheated!) until beef is saucy and cooked through, ~{30-35%minutes}.
(For 4 servings, bake two trays side by side on top rack.)
TIP: Place tray on a foil-lined #baking sheet{} to catch any drips!

Remove tray with chili from oven. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Divide chili between #bowls{}; top with @cheddar cheese{1/2%cup} and @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon}. Serve.

> Ground Meat is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.